However, the following months have shown that Bush's strategy, which was the recommendations of campaign commanders, was the only possible and likely to be successful so that newspapers today do not speak of Iraq at all.
This did not improve Bush's reputation, that said, objectively speaking, he left his successor a final situation far more favourable than could be expected.
Barack Obama hopes that in Afghanistan, the miracle will reproduce
Again, it was the campaign commanders who called for an increase in the military contingent, including the commander of the Afghan operation, General Stanley McCristal, who even severely criticized the restraints of the White House despite the habit of subordination.
He called for 40,000 men to make the situation more favourable.
The president hesitated for three months but without a better option, he cheated on at least the general of 10,000 soldiers.
He managed to remove the promise of an additional 5,000 from Europe, even though it had about 10,000 originally.
What brings the most problems throughout Obama's strategy seems to be his intention to remove the armies of Afghanistan in 18 months and to complete this whole process in three years' time. Obama's entire doctrine brings more questions than it provides answers.
Many doubt the fact that a half increase will bring the same fruit as the progress in Iraq.
Despite the fratricidal wars of recent years, the Iraqi society is relatively well organized and its leaders honor the agreements.
The situation in Afghanistan is marked by the opposite - no one can count on, and no treaty is respected.
Under these conditions, it is difficult to prepare Afghan security forces, who are used to changing their day-to-day leadership according to what arranges them.
Political institutions, although officially founded, will only remain powder in the eyes behind which will proliferate patriarchal ethnic relations.
It is particularly complex to balance the interests of various ethnic groups in view of the lack of clarity in relation to reports, which are still complicated by Pakistani and Iranian influences.
Even the foundation of a "early state to act", which is the basic purpose of the operation, does not seem to be very real.
The temporal horizon of Obama's strategy makes her voluntarism perplexed.
In the past eight years, the situation in Afghanistan has only become worse and is currently on the brink of chaos.
Only a purely romantic heart and out of reality can be persuaded that the small soldiers sent in the tumult of the war for their "early return to the house" will bring there a true miracle.
From a political point of view, setting a date for the withdrawal of troops is purely irresponsible, since the Taliban will regard it as the indirect confession of the US defeat.
NATO's last summit showed that the willingness of Europeans to participate in military operations in Afghanistan is moving towards the negative.
European policies do not know or want to explain to their voters how security in Germany or Italy is linked to a war in the mountains of Hindu Kush.
Another factor that can radically alter the situation is the evolution of events related to Iran.
If the situation continues to deteriorate and the increased sanctions have no effect on Iranians, Americans will face the very difficult issue of a resolution of the problem through the use of military force.
For example, it will be necessary to respond to this when, according to Obama, America is coming to the victorious withdrawal of Afghan troops.
However, each solution of this type will lead to a dramatic reversal of the Afghan situation.
The only Rustine for Obama is the fact that it remains three years until the presidential elections and therefore there is still enough time for it to plan a new strategy, in case it turns out to be a total fiasco.
